  "text": "this zone of highly strained rocks. Medium to high-grade metamorphic rocks (presumably derived from Indian Basement rocks) make up the core of the syntaxis and were once structurally below the Transhimalayan Plutonic Belt. They are dominantly migmatitic gneisses of Proterozoic initial age (Zhang and others, 1992; Burg and others, 1997) . According to [CITATION_1] , they can be divided into a granulite group in the north and an amphibolite group in the south, with the former thrust over the latter by the Namula thrust system.",
